caption: Exceptional plant-based menu, wish they had a recipe book.  Enjoyed the cheese sandwich onsite, and brought pita and hummus home.  Look forward to tasting their eggplant!

I can’t get enough of their delicious food.  I’ve thoroughly enjoyed everything on the menu.  The dishes are well presented and the ingredients are all very fresh.  Try the Buffalo “Chicken” Tacos. They’re amazing.  A word of caution - the humus is addictive.  So great to see this restaurant staying busy in the midst of a pandemic.  All the best to them.  I hope they’re here in Frederick for many years to come!
We love this place! Excellent and affordable vegan food, great kombucha that's not at all vinegary, and a friendly staff that takes COVID-safety really seriously. One of our favorites in town.
Always great. I have been ordering from them a long time when I lived in Frederick. Whenever I am in town I have to have a Buddha salad.

I'm literally writing this review on my phone while holding a freshly made panini in my other hand. The panini & kombucha were a perfect combo for a sunny day. I actually discovered this gem while i passing through town during a long road trip. I was immediately impressed by flavor and quality of the ingredients. Will definitely come back to try dishes!
Great vegetarian option right on market street

I had buffalo chick n ranch sandwich. It tasted different than usual burgers at American restaurants and I liked it. To go/pickup is only option (could be because of pandemic).  I stopped here on my way from greenbrier state park to Baltimore, decided based on reviews. After tasting I felt I always choose good 🤓  (Flowers picture)it’s on the seating table in-front of the restaurant.

100% plant based, vegan, local, organic, homemade, and I feel amazing every time I eat it. I basically live off of this food. I appreciate a small business who lifts up other small businesses (local farm partners! cool retail items!). They publicly follow health guidelines for COVID-19, asking for conscious mask usage of customers and workers alike. I’m really grateful for this place.
Love their curry coconut hummus.
Amazing, as always. Try the coconut curry hummus, it's the best! Love the buffalo chickpea sandwich, the bread is so good!!

Been excited to go here twice and disappointed both times. Hummus is thin. Takes quite awhile. This time the hummus wrap was tiny (I mean, like 5 or 6 bites) for the price ($13). People are nice, though.

Hippy Chick is my favorite spot Downtown Frederick and working there has made it even more of a favorite. Erika is amazing and loves her business, her employees, and her customers. Plus, the food is incredible. Worth going out of your way for!
We got the Falafel Wrap and Buffalo Chick’n Ranch Sandwich and it was LIFE CHANGING. So delicious. Rachael brought it out to us and she was so sweet.  Can’t wait to return next time we’re in town.

The lentil sub is so delicious! I've gotten it three times and it has quickly become my favorite meal (which is saying something given the other exquisite items on the menu). I have also been getting the 'Nana bowls to go and they're the perfect dessert (add the strawberries!) and keep well if you cannot finish it all in one sitting.

Erika is extremely unprofessional, rude, and catty to her employees. She forces them to play the hunger games for their shifts, and then penalizes them for not fulfilling her demands by cutting their hours further. She oversteps her right as a business owner by dictating what and where her employees can do/go outside of the scope of their employment, and frequently humiliates her employees. I have worked in multiple small businesses and I understand that when the economy falls, small businesses take the hit, but using fear tactics on your employees to deal your anxiety and stress is not the way to run a business. Otherwise, the food served here is delicious, ethically sourced, and healthy (though high in sodium). I wish I didn’t know about the unhealthy work environment, because I always loved this place beforehand, and I would have given it 5 starts.  **This review is my original take away, and not endorsed by any past, present, or future employee**
Holy wow! Had my first golden milk latte. So good! Buffalo cauliflower and savory waffle were super yummy!
Wonderful hummus, vegetarian fare, and kombucha (from the Kombucha Lady). Super friendly service. We had the coconut curry hummus and it was smooth and creamy and sublime. Recommended!
Meh
Great vegan options. Everything is made fresh and taste great

"When it's got the food in the name, you get the food." Hippy Chick Hummus is a very health conscious offering, and by far the best hummus I have ever had. Their Coconut Curry is my favorite hummus of all time and has caused me to drive out of my way to get it numerous times. Their Everything Bagel hummus is my second favorite. I cannot speak to their hot food offerings, but aside from their hummus, I found their açaí bowls to be fresh and refreshing. Hippy Chick Hummus is the number one reason I visit Frederick!
my food looked and tasted incredible, i loved the local produce and how healthy & still indulgent everything was. def try anything with their buffalo cauliflower!
I love the food and kombucha here. It’s a really neat spot downtown. The people that work there are really sweet and helpful.
I met someone there and ate outside. The staff follow safety precautions. The food was fantastic, as usual. I got two containers of hummus to take home. The pumpkin cookie was quite tasty.

After walking around on a damp and chilly day, the pumpkin chickpea chili totally hit the spot - flavorful, thick, and comforting. The jalapeno cornbread was perfect with it. I love that everything is vegan! Great customer service, too!

I was super excited to try this restaurant since I am a pescatarian, who abides by a plant-based eating regimen. The service was great, and the young lady who assisted me was nice. I had the roasted broccoli wrap, which was pretty good. It could've been better, but it definitely wasn't bad. One of my main issues revolved around the wait time. We were informed that we would only have to wait 15 minutes, when in reality, we ended up waiting for 30+ minutes. It was quite frustrating. The other downside was with my mom's buffalo chicken sandwich. It was overly salty, and we specifically requested to have the sauce placed on the side, but it was still put on top of the patty, which only intensified the saltiness. She couldn't even eat it because of how overbearing the salt was. This really concerned and disappointed us. Overall, my experience was decent. The service was the best highlight since the young lady did cheerfully assist us; however,  the food, unfortunately, fell beneath my expectations.
I love this place. Too bad it's in Frederick
Never had a bad time here. The food is super fresh, the kombucha is delicious and the service is always personable, attentive and quick.
Hippy Chick Hummus is our families favorite for many reasons. We love the atmosphere as much as we love the food. We love the Hummus Tacos and Allll the smoothie bowls! HIGHLY recommend!
Very cute establishment with good food. Açaí bowl is very good! Great service! My new go to spot in Frederick.
Pretty tasty food, especially for the price! The real draw for me was the kombucha on tap, and it didn’t disappoint. So delicious.
I love this place, and it's worth the drive from Leesburg. Food and service are fantastic.
Delicious!
Great place really enjoyed the food, though some pointers a fork would be nice. Just a thought more than two pitas would be better for an 8 oz container of hummus.

Flavorful, fresh, local, guilt free.  Two picnic tables in the back (colorful!😍), two small bistro tables in the front.  Each have an umbrella for shade.  Sanitizer & wipes readily available.   Self-serve Ice water.  Delicious, locally brewed Kombucha.

Vegan, fresh, delicious.

Their falafel is legit
Yummy
Staff is very friendly and welcoming. The Market Street Tacos with chipotle hummus were very satisfying. I can't wait to return and try the buffalo cauliflower tacos.
Good food and nice staff.
Great tasty vegan food, will definitely go back for more👍👍👍
Extra special food
Always friendly, always something new to try each time I am there.  Food is delicious and the atmosphere is so comforting.

Great service and delicious food! I'm an unhealthy, carnivorous eater, yet I loved the falafel wrap. The spicy sweet potato soup was incredible, and it left my mouth on fire. I'll definitely be going back!
Great food, quaint atmosphere,  lovely staff, highly recommend this place
Friendly staff! Healthy and fresh! So happy to find this gem!
great vegan food, many good & healthy options, always interesting specials.  cute little place, not much inside seating, and a nice little back patio.
I got the pizza. It was really good. My wife got a salad and it was amazing too.

Delicious! The 3 flavors of hummus available were Garlic, Coconut Curry and Chipotle. All my favorites, so hard to choose!  I went with the Chipotle on their sandwich special of the day, which was carrott bacon and more veggies on sprouted bread. The bread looked like a waffle and was toasted and delicious! Nice and spicy! Great flavors!  I chose Fries with tahini sauce with instead of the salad option. Very good and super filling without feeling overstuffed.  I look forward to visiting again next time I go through Frederick!
Yummy and cozy.

Delicious food, helpful and friendly staff, charming atmosphere. I'd recommend Hippy Chick for anybody looking to duck into a delectable local restaurant that exemplifies what Downtown Frederick is all about, whether you're vegan or not!
Earthy goodness!
Delicious
Great vegan choices and local made kombucha. Always enjoy the soup they have.

I was disappointed. I ordered the falafel salad. When I think of a salad, I think the veggies should be cold and fresh.  The tomatoes and cucumbers were warm and wilted, like they were sitting out.  The falafel itself was underwhelming. I would have liked the falafel to be crispy and larger. They were limp, mushy, and unsatisfying. Meh.
Expensive, food was just ok.
So amazing! Had the avocado toast special and loved it, I wish the portions were a little bit bigger for the price but the food is truly incredible.
Amazing food and great staff!

I love the idea behind this restaurant, and reading the story as to how it came to be.  It's a cute space. A bit small if you're dining in.  I ordered the Buffalo Cauliflower Tacos and didn't anticipate how spicy they really were. 🔥  Ended up swapping my plate for my husband's tamer Market Street Tacos.  They were good and I probably would have liked the buffalo ones too if they hadn't have been so overwhelming.  The Coconut Fudge Bites I really enjoyed. Just wish the price wasn't as high.  Same with the Organic Lemonade. Overpriced for something not made in house.  Overall, wonderful concept. Good food, just know what you're ordering. Overpriced add-ons. Small space.

I am not a vegan or a vegetarian and do not even play one on t.v. but this place is one of my FAVORITE restaurants.  The hummus is made fresh and there are different flavors to choose from, but this place is more than Hummus. Try the Avocado Toast and the tacos. I literally eat those tacos once a week. There is also kombucha on tap and you can buy a growler that you can refill and take with you.  Seriously, be curious, not judgemental and check this place out. You will be so happy that you did.
I tried hummus for the first time and loved it

An absolutely adorable little eatery. The owners were super friendly and seemed to be passionate about providing good, healthy vegan food. I had the three hummus tacos with a different flavor hummus on each of them. My favorite was the coconut curry hummus but they were all delicious.  The newly finished patio was quiet, cute, colorful, and cozy.  I highly recommend this place and would definitely return.
Loved the draft kombucha & buddha bowl! It's refreshing to see a menu that's totally gluten free & vegan!
Delicious! We ordered a host of items (Buddha Bowl, Broccoli flat bread, vegan pizza, and hummus sampler) and even left with some hummus for later. We will definitely go back!
This isn't Sabra. They have unique flavors like Chesapeake. Decent prices, and a nice store. You can also buy their stuff at local grocery stores.
Great vegan hummus option to visit.
Very good, 2nd time there and food was amazing,  great place for plant based meals, has fresh kombucha on tap. So good!
Hometown goodness
AMAZING TACOS!! they were so yummy, the staff was so friendly , good energy , cute spot. Definitely returning ☺️☺️☀️

Can be a bit pricy but maybe not. You do get what you pay for, high quality fresh ingredients. The food is always great and the changing hummus flavors are always fantastic.  I have been there mutliple times and will be back again. Highly recommend.
Delicious!
Delicious vegan options

Hippy Chick Hummus is much more than your standard vegan shop, and it's not just because of the food (which is amazing!). From the first second you walk through the doors and are greeted by one of the workers, you feel truly welcome.  This tiny little shop has such a unique and amazing vibe that I've found no where else in this world. Maybe it's the notes, ideas, and words of wisdom that many of the previous patrons scribbled down and suck on the cork boards or underneath the glass table. Maybe it's the art and photography hanging on the walls - all for sale - allowing you to support the local artists who created them. Maybe it's the books on the shelf available for you to browse through while enjoying your meals there. Maybe it's the plants growing in the windows and outside the shop, the beautiful chalk art along the alley leading to the picnic area out back, the lovely workers who seem super happy to be working there and to be creating healthy, sustainable, locally grown meals (EVERYTHING is beautifully garnished by the way, even the drinks!).  The truth is that it's all these things combined that make Hippy Chick such an incredible space. Beyond that, they are locally owned, the food is all made in-house and is very reasonably priced, there are daily specials (Taco Tuesdays!!), and they host really unique events!  Stop in for a meal sometime, I promise you will not regret it! It might even become your new favorite spot in town :)  P.S. Their t-shirts are super soft and great quality. Take a close look at the mandala on the front of it sometime, it'll blow your mind! The creativity is off the charts at this place...
They give you what they advertised. Great place for hummus.
Small place and easy to miss. But those food are taste good.
LOVE this place!  Food is always fresh, so consistent, delicious, and I can always feel good eating it knowing the care they put into selecting their ingredients.
The coconut curry hummus is super on the tacos!
The food was pretty good. The problem is the restaurant was really REALLY dirty when I went. The tables and floors were sticky,  and there was a hair in my bowl.
Wonderful place that provides unique options! I would highly recommend Hippy Chick Hummus as a must go to spot in Frederick!

Really cool shop. It's a small store front so it's easy to miss, but you definitely want to keep an eye out for this spot. Super friendly people, fresh produce, meals made right in front of you, great concept over all.

This fantastic little eatery is just what you need for a healthy and filling lunch. The eclectic interior design pushes the mood of Hippy Chick into a comfy and enjoyable experience. They even have a drawing station to let your creativity flow.  Try to the locally made kombucha along side of a delicious hummus or falafel bowl.
Great staff! So friendly.
Great peaceful envioroment! Owner and employees are excellent. The food is amazing. One of the best spot in Frederick Downtown! Also a great place to support the locals!

I love this place. It's super tiny so there's not much seating. It's downtown so you probably have to pay for parking. But it's worth it. I got a falafel bowl. The falafel was amazing, rolled in hemp seeds I think. It has such fresh veggies in it. And the hummus was amazing obvs. The girl working there was super nice. I personally like the other hummus place in Frederick better.  Theirs was good but not great.

This place is amazing with great atmosphere. I am not vegan or vegetarian but I love their food which is all vegan. The hummus is to die for! My favorites are the garlic, coconut curry, and the Old Bay flavors. I have been there twice before and my third time was last night for dreamcatcher weaving event and it was so much fun. The gluten free pizza was surprisingly better than I imagined but if you want a drink it's either lemonade or Kombucha! Very hippy... I mean limited drink menu.
The food is amazing! Visiting from out of town and I can’t eat gluten and I’m vegan. So I was so glad to find delicious food I can eat! My mom who isn’t vegan loved to too.

This is a cool little place located on North Market Street.  That has a vibe as cool as its name.  Yes, I would describe it as a vegan restaurant with Kombucha on tap.  There's a wonderful selection of bowls with cleaver flavor  combinations.
Owner is a nice person.   Very nice place.
I *LOVE* this place! Always has delicious gluten and dairy free food options. And locally brewed kombucha on tap!! Always delicious and the staff is always wonderful
Definitely worth trying.
Small menu always has yummy food.
Great fresh food,  healthy  options and satisfying.  Enjoyed and will go again.
This place is delicious! My new favorite spot in Frederick. Definitely try the pizza!

Best vegan place    even for non vegan people please come check it out.

Their in house hummus is sooooo good, I seriously didn't think it could be that good but WOW -- I had a buddha bowl with coconut curry hummus today and I absolutely loved it. A Frederick staple!

A cute, cozy place to grab a delicious healthy meal. Don't let the small menu trick you, the food is full of flavor. I enjoyed the Falafel Bowl (with the spicy option). It had a good level of heat, without being overbearing, with a tahini sauce and fresh veggies. It came with their homemade Spicy Hummus, and it could have easily been the main part of my meal, it was so good! The entire place is very small, but we were able to find seating right away. They have kombucha on tap, which I've never seen before so it was a fun treat. I tried the Cherry Blossom Kombucha, which was light and fizzy without being too sweet. I highly recommend!
Totally enjoyed the food

Amazing lunch, exciting flavours, wholesome, healthy and very satisfying! Recommend the blackberry kombucha. Delicious :) got the chick-peaza which featured a cashew cheese and tahini dressing. Don't need meat to get your protein with this kind of tasty super food!
Super friendly employees and a unique menu.  Amazing spicy hummus and a delicious banana dessert I couldn’t even begin to make a dent in.  #eatlocal
Fresh delicious hummus and amazing kombucha!
